---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Troubleshooting · Squeezy"
  description="Concrete Squeezy diagnostics, feedback, report, provider, permission, and session recovery workflows."
  activeDoc="/docs/troubleshooting/"
  eyebrow="support"
  heading="Collect local evidence before opening an issue."
  lead="Start with the command that matches the failure. Use report previews for diagnostics, and keep private code and secrets out of public GitHub issues."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Fast path</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">install/config</span>
        <h3>Run doctor first</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy doctor</code></pre>
        <p>Use this for startup, provider credentials, local storage, sandbox, and basic environment failures.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">effective config</span>
        <h3>Inspect merged settings</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy config inspect</code></pre>
        <p>Use this when a setting behaves differently than expected. Sensitive values are redacted.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">local docs</span>
        <h3>Ask built-in help</h3>
        <pre><code>/help
/help providers
/help permissions
/help sessions</code></pre>
        <p>Use this for setup questions before spending provider tokens on a general model answer.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Feedback and report commands</h2>
    <div class="matrix">
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3><code>/feedback</code></h3></div>
        <p>Short feedback from inside the TUI. Best for copy issues, confusing UI, small product suggestions, or a problem that does not need logs.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">lightweight</span>
      </article>
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3><code>/report</code></h3></div>
        <p>Current-session diagnostic report. Best for a failed run, bad provider response, confusing tool behavior, permission denial, or broken resume.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">current session</span>
      </article>
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3><code>squeezy sessions report &lt;id&gt; --preview</code></h3></div>
        <p>Preview a redacted report for a past session before upload. Check paths, prompts, command summaries, and metadata before sending.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">preview first</span>
      </article>
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3><code>squeezy sessions report &lt;id&gt; --send</code></h3></div>
        <p>Send the report after preview. Include the returned report id in a GitHub issue instead of attaching private archives publicly.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">send after review</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>What to include in a public issue</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">environment</span>
        <h3>Platform and version</h3>
        <p>Operating system, install path, Squeezy version or commit, provider route, and whether the issue is reproducible in a clean repo.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">symptom</span>
        <h3>Exact failure shape</h3>
        <p>The command or prompt that failed, the visible error message, and whether retrying changed the behavior.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">diagnostic id</span>
        <h3>Report or feedback id</h3>
        <p>Use the id returned by `/feedback`, `/report`, or `squeezy sessions report`. Do not paste private code, secrets, or full archives.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button" href={SITE.issuesUrl} data-track-click="troubleshooting_issues" data-track-target="github">Open GitHub issues</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Common checks</h2>
    <div class="matrix">
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3>Provider failures</h3></div>
        <p>Run `squeezy config inspect`, confirm the active provider/model, check the expected API key or OAuth file, and retry with a simple prompt.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">model route</span>
      </article>
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3>Permission prompts</h3></div>
        <p>Inspect `[permissions]`, shell sandbox settings, outside-workspace paths, MCP/web access, and whether the action is destructive.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">policy</span>
      </article>
      <article class="matrix-row">
        <div><h3>Session resume issues</h3></div>
        <p>Use the resume picker, then generate a past-session report with `squeezy sessions report &lt;id&gt; --preview` if state looks wrong.</p>
        <span class="status-pill">sessions</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
